This paper deals with the problem of recognizing interval bigraphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions the use of decomposition techniques, which is a common theme in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
